      "cardText": "SHAME SPIRAL CARD: Phone notification sound\n\n1) WHAT HAPPENED NOW\nEnvironment: Any digital environment\nTrigger: Phone notification sound\n\n2) THE OLD TRAUMA STORY\n“Something urgent/dangerous is coming”\n\n3) WHAT SHAME MAY SAY\n“I am unsafe because I failed to see the danger early enough.”\n\n4) BODY SIGNALS\nstartle, heart jump\n\n5) DEFAULT PROTECTION PATTERN\nfight | Arousal: mixed | Risk: 🟢 Low\n\n6) OLD ORIGIN THIS MAY ECHO\nOld attachment alarm: absence, delay, or ambiguity felt like rejection or punishment.\n\n7) WHAT IS MORE TRUE\nA trigger is a signal, not a verdict. This reaction makes sense, and I can check present evidence before I obey shame.\n\n8) RE-PARENTING RESPONSE\nProtect without attacking. Put both feet down and delay the next sentence by one breath.\n\n9) REPAIR STEP\nDo the grounding step first: Turn off non-essential alerts; assign notification windows. Then write one sentence: 'The shame said __, but the present evidence says __.'\n\n10) PARTNER / CLINICIAN RESPONSE\nLower your voice, pause the argument, and name safety: 'I am not here to attack you. We can slow this down.'\n\n11) PAKISTAN / CULTURAL NOTE\nHigh relevance in Pakistan/cultural contexts; adapt examples to WhatsApp use, family systems, gender expectations, work hierarchy, religion, privacy, and stigma.\n\n12) USE THIS MODULE\nDigital Nervous System",
